examples.solution:
1. Use quadratic formula: x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
2. Substitute a=3, b=8, c=-5: x = \frac{-8 \pm \sqrt{64 - 4(3)(-5)}}{6}
3. Simplify: x = \frac{-8 \pm \sqrt{124}}{6}
4. Calculate roots: x \approx 0.52 or x \approx -3.19

